<m0> Russian legislators who toured Tallahassee were particularly interested in the debate over free meals. They consider the salary that Florida lawmakers get (about $24,000 a year) to be a pretty good privilege since most of them are unpaid.<ep>
  ``There isn't a formal, professional lobby'' in his legislature, says <m0>Aleksandr Osipov,<m0> speaking through an interpreter. ``If somebody tries to bribe you, he usually does it under the table.''<ql>
