<m0>  A crowd gathered around Rep. Meek in the House chambers. But it wasn't Rep. <m0>Kendrick Meek, <m0>D-Miami, who had the lawmakers so fascinated. It was the other representative in the family (--) U.S. Rep. <m0>Carrie Meek<m0>, D-Fla. (--) in town for the 50th anniversary of her graduation from Florida A & M University.<ep>
  Meek, the son, gladly gave up the microphone to his mother, and asked her to demonstrate her infamous battle cry from her legislative days<ep>
  Meek, the mom, was happy to oblige. Waving a black flag stamped with a skull-and-crossbones, she invoked the threat of old: ``I'm going to kill that bill Black Flag dead!'' <ql>
