<m0>HOG WILD<ql>
<m1><styl>vs,1 <styl>kr,0 <styl>pf,14,celi<ql>
<m0>Session's final days<ql>
resemble the hunt<ql>
<m1><styl>vs,4 <styl>txt,11p1 <styl>ragx<ql>
<styl>indentl,2l,0,4l,3.5p<ql>
<styl>txt,11p1<ql>
<ep>
<m0> With hundreds of bills left to consider, the last days of the session may resemble a wild hog hunt as described by <m0>James Harold Thompson,<m0> lawyer, lobbyist and one of the wisest House speakers in recent times. Thompson, riding in a Capitol elevator to the lobbyist-filled rotunda, was explaining his son's fervor for hunting wild hog.<ep>
  It takes one set of baying hounds to trap the hog, then a bulldog to rush in and pull him down. The hunter follows. By the time the hunter arrives, he is hip-deep in water because that's where the hog seeks shelter. The hunter lifts the hog by the tail and ties his two rear legs. Half the trick here is keeping the dogs away from the hog.<ql>
